text:
Looks great! Few things.
 - first slide, instead of calling it 'ቫይረስ', use the term 'በትንፋሽ የሚተላለፍ በሽታ'.
 - second side, I feel one and two should be combined
 - third screen - keep hands away from face. (The virus stays on different surfaces for different amount of time)

Another way to see the isolation part is as protecting the more vulnerable people mentioned under the fourth screen. So maybe throw something in there to show case that so the less vulnerable can respect this and stay isolated and careful.

Also during this time, supporting the isolated people is another way to prevent spread. Trying as much as possible to eliminate the need for infected individuals from going out by neighbors providing them basic help, like delivery or food/medicine purchase. So a page that shows compassion would be a great addition.

text:
Hello Everyone,
Misinformation is a huge and often overlooked issue. That is what we should battle. 
The situation is consistently changing. Reports of how it is transmitted, how it can be prevented and the like are changing. Everyone is posting their thoughts. 
The campaign’s aim is to build a central, referable, practical, and context-adapted set of information regarding the virus and its prevention. 
The idea is for others to add to the information on the campaign, not to use that only. 
Feel free to adapt the color changes, share it on your personal social media platforms/ share it with others and as much as possible give credit where its due especially for Tarikua Erda whose article assisted the making of this campaign.

We hope it helps, we really do.
Entire campaign information: <https://bit.ly/COVID19CampaignInformation>
Social media posts along with captions are found here: <https://bit.ly/COVIDD19CampaignSocial>
